ResourceHeader.Description: NASA's Explorer 33 spacecraft, also known as Anchored IMP (AIMP) A and as IMP E, was launched into a geocentric orbit in July, 1966. (A lunar-centered had been intended.) Lunar perturbations caused significant variations in orbit parameters, with apogee ranging between 70 and 135 Re. Measurements of thermal plasma, energetic particles, magnetic fields and solar X-rays were made. No data were obtained after October, 1971.
